#Import Data

# full path to the data files
data1 <- here::here("TRIAL03")

#read list of files in the folder
files <- list.files (path = data1)
#read first spectrum to buffor, column separator is comma here
#IMPORTANT check what is the separator in your data file
#and change accordingly in row with command read.table
#typical values are space " " coma "," or tab "\t" - below coma
buffer <- read.table (file.path(data1,files [1 ]), sep= "," )
#allocate matrix number of columns is equal the number of rows
#in spectrum file number of rows is equal the number of spectra files
spc <- matrix ( ncol = nrow (buffer), nrow = length (files))
#write to first row spectrum number 1
spc [1 , ] <- buffer [, 2 ]
# then rest of the data
for ( f in seq (along = files)[- 1]) {
  buffer <- read.table (file.path(data1,files [f ]), sep= ",")
  spc [f, ] <- buffer[, 2]
}
# X-axis vector
wavenumber = buffer [, 1 ]
#vector with additional data

# time of the experiment
t1 = as.numeric (substring(files,20,25))
#time difference between  the points
z1 <- strptime(t1, "%H%M%S")
dif1=diff (z1)
#cumulative difference in seconds, 0 added at the beginning
dif2=data.frame (as.numeric(c( 0, cumsum(as.numeric (dif1)))))
colnames(dif2)=c( "time")


d = data.frame(files, t1,z1,dif2)
colnames(d)=c("name","t1", "z1", "dif")



#Create hyperspec
hyper01<-new ("hyperSpec", wavelength = wavenumber, spc = spc, data= d)
hyper01

#normalize 2 (data between 0 and 1)

normalize2 <- function(x){
  return((x-min(x)) / (max(x)-min(x)))
}

subset03<-subset01%>%dplyr::group_by(.wavelength)%>% mutate(spcN2 = normalize2(spc))

# extract data to HCA analysis observations in rows
wide01<-as.wide.df(hyper01s)

names01<-wide01[,4]
wide02<-wide01[,-c(1:5)]
rownames(wide02)<-names01

# Dissimilarity matrix

distance <- dist(wide02, method = "euclidean")
# Hierarchical clustering using wards Linkage
hc1 <- hclust(distance, method = "ward.D2" )

dend <- as.dendrogram(hc1)
plot(dend)

pdf("Dendrogram_4_clusters.pdf", width=8, height = 4) # Open a new pdf file

corr2D test

 data01<-hyper01s$spc
 #wavenumber01<-seq(from=3996, to=520, by=-1)
 wavenumber01<-seq(from=520, to=3996, by=1)
 twod<-corr2d(data01, Wave1=wavenumber01)
## HOMO-Correlation: 4 cores used for calculation
## 22:50:45 - using mean values as reference
